content.text: Review this Horse Chooser wizard page at 325px width (small phone). The first 3 images show the wizard form state (no chat), and images 4-8 show the AI-generated horse recommendations with Top 3 picks. Check for: 1. Layout overflow - anything extending past viewport? 2. Touch targets - buttons/links at least 44px? 3. Text readability - font sizes adequate? 4. Navigation buttons - easy to use? 5. Quick option buttons - properly sized and laid out? 6. Horse cards in results - properly laid out with stats readable? Images fitting well? 7. Chat bubble / AI response formatting? Be specific about any issues. Include CSS selectors if possible.
